{"title": "What is a DVA Patient?", "body": "The Department of Veterans Affairs (DVA) is the main agency that provides services and creates programs to help veterans and the defence force communities.\nA DVA Patient is someone acknowledged by DVA to get specific benefits in healthcare, like discounted medications through the Repatriation Pharmaceutical Benefits Scheme (RPBS).\nTo learn how to create a DVA Patient Record, click here:\nHow to Create a DVA Patient Record\n    If you need further assistance please contact support on 1300 103 903 or email at support@medirecords.com"}